There is data limitation
both on type and quality.

01:09:59.375 --> 01:10:02.990
We observed that in
many of the measurements

01:10:02.990 --> 01:10:05.340
and in many of the
decision making,

01:10:05.340 --> 01:10:06.890
there is lots of
uncertainty that

01:10:06.890 --> 01:10:11.610
is related to quality of
data and limitations of data.

01:10:11.610 --> 01:10:14.180
So hopefully, with
the new generations

01:10:14.180 --> 01:10:19.250
of passively-collected data
that are nowadays introduced,

01:10:19.250 --> 01:10:25.460
there will be improvement
in the existing practice

01:10:25.460 --> 01:10:28.520
to take advantage of that
data and improve the planning

01:10:28.520 --> 01:10:30.080
process.

01:10:30.080 --> 01:10:33.000
Again, measures not always
closely tied to objectives.

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:39.700
That's something that
is relevant to what

01:10:39.700 --> 01:10:44.570
Adishak mentioned in terms
of some of these measures

